tListenerSupport, as it handles read/write internally. I should check if it only serializes listeners that are actually serializable. The documentation might be helpful here. While Apache SerializationUtils.clone requires serializable objects, EventListenerSupport does implement Serializable, meaning it should allow for cloning. However, maybe utilizing direct Java Object streams would be simpler and more straightforward for testing. I’ll need to run specific tests to validate this.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing serialization challenges**\\n\\nI need to read line 320 through deserialization and check if the listeners are serializable, noting whether they are package-private or public. I might face issues with native image serialization of lambdas, so I should use classes instead. There's a potential concern with EventListenerSupport's readObject method that may skip nonserializable listeners. I'll test the deserialization process to see if the original and deserialized listeners work as expected. Additionally, using a mutable list for serializable listeners could be beneficial, but I need to ensure the sizes match during testing.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying interface serialization**\\n\\nI’m considering if the listener interface should extend Serializable. If it does, then I'll need to think about implementations that might not be serializable. Actually, I realize that a class implementing a subinterface of Serializable is considered Serializable, even without explicit declaration. So, I conclude that the listener interface itself should not extend Serializable; only the implementation needs to handle that. This distinction is key, and it feels good to clarify this!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_p3lBeaZwY2ahvo1jwLzrbekQ|fc_027075d6ca715063016a297281fb9881968556318e52a4773b", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.commons/commons-lang3/3.20.0/src/test/java/org_apache_commons/commons_lang3/EventListenerSupportTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_apache_commons.commons_lang3;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\nimport java.io.Serializable;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.List;\n\nimport org.apache.commons.lang3.event.EventListenerSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class EventListenerSupportTest {\n\n    @Test\n    public void serializationRoundTripKeepsSerializableListenersAndDropsNonSerializableListeners()\n            throws IOException, ClassNotFoundException {\n        EventListenerSupport<AuditListener> listenerSupport = EventListenerSupport.create(AuditListener.class);\n        SerializableAuditListener serializableListener = new SerializableAuditListener(\"persisted\");\n        NonSerializableAuditListener nonSerializableListener = new NonSerializableAuditListener(\"transient\");\n\n        listenerSupport.addListener(serializableListener);\n        listenerSupport.addListener(nonSerializableListener);\n        listenerSupport.fire().onAudit(\"before-serialization\");\n\n        EventListenerSupport<AuditListener> deserializedListenerSupport = roundTrip(listenerSupport);\n        AuditListener[] restoredListeners = deserializedListenerSupport.getListeners();\n\n        assertThat(restoredListeners).hasSize(1);\n        assertThat(restoredListeners[0]).isInstanceOf(SerializableAuditListener.class);\n\n        SerializableAuditListener restoredListener = (SerializableAuditListener) restoredListeners[0];\n        assertThat(restoredListener.events()).containsExactly(\"persisted:before-serialization\");\n\n        deserializedListenerSupport.fire().onAudit(\"after-deserialization\");\n\n        assertThat(restoredListener.events())\n                .containsExactly(\"persisted:before-serialization\", \"persisted:after-deserialization\");\n        assertThat(nonSerializableListener.events()).containsExactly(\"transient:before-serialization\");\n    }\n\n    @SuppressWarnings(\"unchecked\")\n    private static EventListenerSupport<AuditListener> roundTrip(final EventListenerSupport<AuditListener> listenerSupport)\n            throws IOException, ClassNotFoundException {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream byteArrayOutputStream = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (ObjectOutputStream objectOutputStream = new ObjectOutputStream(byteArrayOutputStream)) {\n            objectOutputStream.writeObject(listenerSupport);\n        }\n\n        try (ObjectInputStream objectInputStream = new ObjectInputStream(\n                new ByteArrayInputStream(byteArrayOutputStream.toByteArray()))) {\n            return (EventListenerSupport<AuditListener>) objectInputStream.readObject();\n        }\n    }\n\n    public interface AuditListener {\n\n        void onAudit(String message);\n    }\n\n    public static final class SerializableAuditListener implements AuditListener, Serializable {\n        private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n\n        private final String name;\n        private final List<String> events = new ArrayList<>();\n\n        public SerializableAuditListener(final String name) {\n            this.name = name;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void onAudit(final String message) {\n            events.add(name + \":\" + message);\n        }\n\n        public List<String> events() {\n            return events;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class NonSerializableAuditListener implements AuditListener {\n\n        private final String name;\n        private final List<String> events = new ArrayList<>();\n\n        public NonSerializableAuditListener(final String name) {\n            this.name = name;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void onAudit(final String message) {\n            events.add(name + \":\" + message);\n        }\n\n        public List<String> events() {\n            return events;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 813, "output": 1537, "cacheRead": 18432, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 20782, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781101167211, "responseId": "resp_027075d6ca715063016a29726fc40081968fb066a1d9ce3f91"}}
